(:summary    "Emacs interface to the Google Translate"
 :repository (git . "https://github.com/avshramko/google-translate-el.git")
 :created    "2011"
 :updated    "2011"
 :authors    (("Andrey Shramko" . "t0mmydnua@yandex.ru"))
 :maintainer ("Andrey Shramko" . "t0mmydnua@yandex.ru")
 :provided   (google-translate)
 :required   ((("emacs" url)))
 :homepage   "https://github.com/avshramko/google-translate-el"
 :commentary "\
You should always be able to find the latest version here:

https://github.com/avshramko/google-translate.el

Note that you need a Google API key to use this; you can
get one by following the instructions here:

https://code.google.com/apis/console/

Usage:
(require 'google-translate)
(setq
 google-translate-api-key \"<API-KEY>\"     ;; You must visit the Google APIs console to get your API key
 google-translate-source-language \"en\"    ;; The source-language is language that the source text is written in
 google-translate-target-language \"ru\"    ;; The target-language is language that the source text is translated into
 google-translate-word-output '(nil)      ;; \\
 google-translate-region-output '(t . t)  ;;  > first (t - output in buffer, nil - output in message)
 google-translate-buffer-output '(t . t)) ;; /  second (t - split horizontally, nil - split vertically)
(global-set-key (kbd \"C-x t\") 'google-translate-word)

Google APIs Console: http://code.google.com/apis/console
Language reference: http://code.google.com/intl/ru/apis/language/translate/v2/using_rest.html#language-params")
